 Governor of Benue, Samuel Otom. Photo/Twitter/benuestategovt  It also disclosed that over 500 illegal structures have been earmarked for demolition across the state. General Manager, Benue State Urban Development Board, Saint Gbilekaa, who stated this in Makurdi, explained that out of the over 500 illegal buildings in the state, at least 300 were in Makurdi. He noted that the board has commenced demolition of illegal structures, especially around the Old Makurdi Bridge, New Garage, Wadata, Wurukum and Benue State University in the state capital. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .